<br>
I keep melee, chem, and alternate the other with ones I keep in a pack.<br>
<br>
If you get your ass in a sling especially with multiple mobs using, use deflection shield that cooresponds to the type of damage they are inflicting.  It can save your butt... <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#FFFFCC><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub83.ezboard.com/bthepunchingbag74708.showLocalUserPublicProfile?login=littlechi>Littlechi</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Ninja Wanna-Be</span><br>  Posts: 1<br> <font color=#660000>(7/31/02 12:32 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub83.ezboard.com/fthepunchingbag74708frm2.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=477.topic&index=7>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Def shield vs parry shield</span><hr size=1> It seems like you are confusing Parry shields with Deflection shields. I have been using both, and here is what i found :<br>
The Parry shield did indeed increasemy armour, and thus helping me in combat when the mob was not doing minimal damage, but the deflection shild did not. Nor did the deflection shield deflect damage back on mob, or my friends when i tested this in PVP. (I have been using shields ql arrond 100) Anyone else found anything similar?<br>
Also the deflection shield use riposte, and the parry shields use parry (big suprise :) ) So to be on the safe side, id go for the Parry shields if you are uncertain, (because of BwT) <br>
Best of luck, will look into this further and post any new findings. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#99CC66><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub83.ezboard.com/bthepunchingbag74708.showUserPublicProfile?gid=autumndawnfire>Autumn Dawnfire</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.melanierawn.com/images/bunnie.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>They call me Bruce.</span><br>  Posts: 217<br> <font color=#660000>(6/16/03 5:43 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub83.ezboard.com/fthepunchingbag74708frm2.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=477.topic&index=8>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> no... i think you're the one confused :)</span><hr size=1> <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :rollin --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/images/emoticons/roll.gif ALT=":rollin"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
<br>
there is no such thing as a &quot;parry shield&quot; in the data base - those of use that know what you mean understand, but to keep any new folks from making a mistake in what their looking for: Deflection Sheilds use the parry skill, the original poster has it dead on <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
<br>
Deflection Shield Projector's ( that last word makes all the difference ) use riposte. <br>
<br>
Defelction Shields are a great panic button and work very very well ( espcially considering you need parry for BwT any how ) - i HIGHLY recommend them <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->   Keep in mind you can hot key them from inventory - so if you really felt like it you could have one for each type of damage hot keyed ( and in inventory ).  It is however, impossible to use the ql 200 Defelction Shields without also using a parry stick ( they add to parry skill oddly enough ).  Even triple implanted and title 6 capped you still need more parry to use ql  200 deflection shield - they add about 5k ac btw.<br>
<br>
Now on Deflection Shield Projector's - the only thing they do is reduce the time on your riposte skill ( which you may have raised for some other ma special like say... Upon a Wave of Summer or Angel of Night ).  If you want to have a few ( very few ) extra points of damage as a reflect pick on up that matches your riposte skil - but by no mean should you go out of yoru way to raise riposte for *this* item.  There is no % reflection of damage as the original text on them indicates - with a riposte skill of over 700 you will stilll only see about 54 points of damage &quot;riposted* back. <p></p><i></i></td></tr></table> </td></tr></table> <table border=0 width=95%><tr><td align=left valign="top"> </td><td align=right valign="top"><a href="http://pub83.ezboard.com/fthepunchingbag74708frm2.showPrevMessage?topicID=477.topic"> << Prev Topic</a>&nbsp;| <a href="http://pub83.ezboard.com/fthepunchingbag74708frm2.showNextMessage?topicID=477.topic"> Next Topic >> </a><br><br><a self href=http://pub83.ezboard.com/fthepunchingbag74708frm2.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=477.topic&index=8><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/themes/far_east/addReply.gif border=0 alt="Add Reply"></a> </td></tr></table><br><table width=95% border=0><td valign="top"> <a href=http://pub83.ezboard.com/fthepunchingbag74708frm2.emailToFriend?topicID=477.topic><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/image/email.gif border=0 alt="Email This To a Friend"> Email This To a Friend</a><br> <a href=http://pub83.ezboard.com/fthepunchingbag74708frm2.threadControl?topicID=477.topic><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/themes/far_east/deleteThread.gif border=0 alt="Topic Control Image"> Topic Commands</a><br> <a href=http://pub83.ezboard.com/fthepunchingbag74708frm2.subscribeUnregisteredToTopic?topicID=477.topic><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/themes/ultimate/subscribe.gif width=20 height=20 border=0 alt="Click to receive email notification of replies"> Click to receive email notification of re